Instruct the GSO to submit to the municipal accountant the RSMI;
Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to conduct physical inventory-taking and reconciliation of Welfare Goods for Distribution inventory account;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to effect correcting entries if a variance is noted in the inventory count;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and the GSO to observe the proper recording and reporting requirements in the prospective management of inventories.

Revisit the staffing pattern of the municipal accounting office for recruitment of staff or temporary augmentation of personnel;
Instruct the municipal accountant for the immediate submission of the updated financial reports and documents; and
Enjoin the Municipal Accountant to strictly enforce the submission of succeeding required financial reports and accounts within the prescribed period.

Require immediate liquidation of all outstanding cash advances as of December 31, 2019 by issuing demand letters to the concerned parties;
Require the issuance of Certification by the Municipal Accountant that the previous cash advance has been liquidated and accounted for in the books before granting a new cash advance; and
Strictly adhere to the provisions on the granting and utilization of cash advances as prescribed by Section 89 of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002.

Direct the Municipal Treasurer with the Local Chief Executive to make a representation to the Department of Finance requesting reconsideration and restructure on the penalties charged for possible reduction of the amount;
Enjoin the responsible officials in the monitoring of loans payable of the LGU to submit a written explanation thru the Local Chief Executive, why the penalty of P1,534,943.58 for late payments of DOF loan should not be a personal liability on their part; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to adjust the financial statements to recognize the unpaid penalties after setting-up appropriate cash back-up for the obligation.

Immediate completion and submission for approval to the National Solid Waste Management Commission of the 10 year SWM Plan as required under RA 9003;
Strict implementation of the prescribed procedures and guidelines under RA 9003 on the solid waste segregation at source;
Convert the LGU’s dumpsite to a Sanitary Landfill in compliance with Section 37 of RA 9003;
Allocate from the Solid Waste Management Fund for the purchase of protective gears and/or equipment for use by the garbage collectors during collection and disposal of solid waste; and
Provide necessary trainings to the collectors and personnel directly dealing with collection of solid waste.

We recommended to expedite implementation and completion of the projects in accordance with the guidelines stated in memorandum of agreement with source agency for timely benefit to constituents;
To instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to conduct reconciliation of records with source agency for proper recognition of fund transfer balances and full liquidation;
To instruct the Municipal Treasurer to return to source agencies all unexpended fund balances on all completed projects otherwise to request for authority to realign said balances for other priority projects; and
To instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw journal entry voucher to record the return as evidenced by the source agency’s official receipt; make reclassification entry to properly recognize the assets on completed projects; and close trust liability accounts on funds duly liquidated.

